reviewText: could of been better and longer

I alway enjoyed Norm Crosby's off-beat, different approach to humor.  I had forgotten over the years how much he made me laugh until I dug out a large collection of VHS tapes of Dean Martin's roasts of celebrities.  I had bought them through the mail. watched a couple, and until recently I had let them gather dust.  Crosby's performance is 37 years old, yet most of the subject matter is still relevant stuff.
A great humorous lesson on how the English language is misused.  It is a great reminder on how we can get lazy when speaking.
The only complaint I have about this DVD is it isn't long enough. Norm  appeared sometimes on the Dean Martin Roasts. His humor is just as good now years later.
